<P>A New Voyage TO ITALY: With a De&s;cription of the Chief <HI>Towns, Churches, Tombs, Libraries, Palaces, Statues,</HI> and <HI>Antiquities</HI> of that Country.</P>
<P>Together with U&s;eful INSTRUCTIONS for tho&s;e who &s;hall Travel thither.</P>
<P>By MAXIMILIAN MISSON, Gent.</P>
<P><HI>Done into</HI> Engli&s;h, <HI>and adorn'd with</HI> FIGURES.</P>
<P>In Two Volumes.</P>
<P>Vol. I.</P>
<P><HI>LONDON,</HI> Printed for <HI>R. Bently,</HI> at the <HI>Po&s;t-Hou&s;e</HI> in <HI>Ru&s;&s;el-&s;treet, Covent-Garden; M. Gillyflower,</HI> at the <HI>Spread-Eagle</HI> in <HI>We&s;tmin&s;ter-Hall; T. Goodwin,</HI> at the <HI>Queen's-Head,</HI> and <HI>M. Wotton,</HI> at the <HI>Three Daggers</HI> in <HI>Fleet-&s;treet;</HI> and <HI>S. Man&s;hip,</HI> at the <HI>Ship</HI> in <HI>Cornhill,</HI> 1695.</P>
